.TH TESSERA 8 "2026-05-13" "0.1.1" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
tessera \- USB session monitor and CLI for Tessera
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tessera daemon
[\fB\-\-config\fR \fIFILE\fR]
[\fB\-\-socket\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-state\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-grace\-seconds\fR \fIN\fR]
[\fB\-\-suspend\-grace\-seconds\fR \fIN\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-udev\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-dbus\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tessera daemon
is a privileged daemon that complements the
.B pam_tessera
PAM module. It listens on a Unix socket for session-open and session-close
notifications from the PAM cdylib, watches udev for USB token removal events,
and subscribes to logind D-Bus signals for suspend, resume, and
session-removed transitions. When a registered token is removed (or the
session ends/suspends past the configured grace window), the daemon enforces
the configured
.B removal-action
(lock, logout, shutdown, or operator hook) for the affected session as
declared in the
.B [monitor]
section of the shared TOML config.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-config \fIFILE\fR
Path to the shared TOML config file (default
.IR /etc/tessera/config.toml ).
Fields under the
.B [monitor]
section populate the daemon's runtime knobs; the CLI flags below override
the corresponding config values when supplied.
.TP
.B \-\-socket \fIPATH\fR
Unix socket path used for IPC with the PAM cdylib. Overrides
.BR monitor.socket_path .
.TP
.B \-\-state\-file \fIPATH\fR
Path to the persisted session registry (JSON). Overrides
.BR monitor.state_file_path .
.TP
.B \-\-grace\-seconds \fIN\fR
Grace window in seconds between USB token removal and execution of the
configured removal action. Overrides
.BR monitor.usb_removed_grace_seconds .
.TP
.B \-\-suspend\-grace\-seconds \fIN\fR
Grace window in seconds applied after system suspend/resume before
re-evaluating token presence. Overrides
.BR monitor.suspend_grace_seconds .
.TP
.B \-\-no\-udev
Skip launching the udev monitor thread. The race-check udev query also
degrades to an always-present stub, so end-to-end tests that disable the
udev thread don't see spurious DEVICE_GONE rejections. Not for production
use.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-dbus
Skip connecting to D-Bus. The actions backend degrades to a no-op
(lock/terminate/power-off requests are logged but never sent) and the
logind signal listener is not started. Production deployments must NEVER
set this \(em the entire purpose of monitord is to enforce removal via
logind.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/tessera/config.toml
Shared validated configuration. The
.B [monitor]
section is consumed by this daemon and must agree with what the PAM
cdylib reads from the same file.
.TP
.I /run/tessera/monitord.sock
Default Unix socket path for IPC between the PAM module and the daemon.
.TP
.I /var/lib/tessera/registry.json
Default persisted session registry; survives daemon restarts so in-flight
sessions are reconciled on resume.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pam_tessera (8),
.BR pam.conf (5),
.BR logind.conf (5)
